-- Head of Mexican Oil Workers Union Re-Elected, Reforma Reports
-- B y   B e n   B a i n
-- 2012-10-20T21:54:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-20/head-of-mexican-oil-workers-union-re-elected-reforma-reports.html
Mexican oil workers union head
Carlos Romero Deschamps was re-elected as head of the group to
serve through 2018, the  Reforma newspaper  reported.  The union boss also is a senator with the Institutional
Revolutionary Party, known as the PRI. Incoming Mexico President
Enrique Pena Nieto, also from that party, has called overhauling
the state-run oil industry his “signature issue.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Bain in Mexico City at 
 bbain2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier in  New York  at 
 swier@bloomberg.net  